## Overview

PerformIQ is a full-stack web application designed to solve a critical gap in retail workforce management — the absence of a structured, data-driven system to measure and motivate employee productivity.

It combines a **normalized analytics engine**, a **geofencing-based attendance system**, and a **gamification layer** to give retail managers actionable insights while keeping employees motivated through XP, levels, badges and leaderboards.

---

## Problem Statement

Current retail store operations suffer from:
- Sales performance shared informally via WhatsApp
- No standardized or normalized productivity scoring
- No structured database for employee performance data
- No real-time analytics or visibility for managers
- Performance evaluation that is subjective rather than data-driven
- Hidden patterns like consistency, growth trends and volatility that go undetected

**Core Problem:** Lack of a quantitative, normalized and structured system to evaluate retail staff productivity.

---

## Key Features

### For Employees
- **Gamified Dashboard** — XP points, levels, badges and streaks
- **Personal Performance View** — weekly productivity score, trend charts, metric breakdown
- **Leaderboard** — ranked view against colleagues
- **Geofenced Attendance** — one-tap punch in/out verified by location

### For Managers
- **Analytics Dashboard** — department-level insights, revenue comparisons, target achievement
- **Live Floor Monitoring** — real-time employee presence status via SSE
- **Employee Clustering** — K-Means based grouping (e.g. High Volume vs High Basket)
- **Performance Alerts** — early identification of underperformers and high-growth employees
- **Correlation Heatmaps** — relationships between metrics across the team

---

## System Architecture

```
React Frontend (PWA)
        ↕  REST API
Node.js + Express Backend
        ↕  SQL queries
SQLite Database (local)
        ↑  reads & writes
Python Analytics Engine
        
Firebase Auth (identity verification only)
        
Server-Sent Events (SSE) — live manager alerts
```

### Data Flow
1. Daily sales data is entered or imported into the database
2. Python analytics script runs weekly, computing all metrics and writing scores back to SQLite
3. Node.js backend exposes REST endpoints, verifies Firebase tokens, queries SQLite
4. React frontend renders dashboards, charts and gamification UI
5. Geofencing location checks run silently via PWA service worker every 30 minutes during a shift

---

## Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|---|---|
| Frontend | React, Tailwind CSS, Recharts |
| Backend | Node.js, Express.js |
| Database | SQLite (via better-sqlite3) |
| Analytics | Python, pandas, numpy, scipy, sklearn |
| Auth | Firebase Authentication |
| Real-time | Server-Sent Events (SSE) |
| Attendance | Browser Geolocation API + PWA Service Worker |

---

## Database Schema

Six core tables:

| Table | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `stores` | Store location and geofence radius |
| `departments` | Department benchmarks for normalization |
| `employees` | Employee profiles linked to Firebase UID |
| `daily_performance` | Daily sales records per employee |
| `attendance` | Punch in/out logs with coordinates and status |
| `location_events` | Background geolocation check audit trail |
| `scores` | Weekly computed productivity scores and XP |
| `badges` | Earned badges per employee |

---

## Performance Metrics

The **Productivity Index** is a normalized 0–100 score computed weekly by the Python analytics engine.

| Metric | Weight | Description |
|---|---|---|
| Revenue vs Target % | 30% | Actual revenue / weekly target |
| Basket Performance Index | 20% | Avg basket size relative to dept average |
| Manager Rating Score | 15% | Weekly avg of daily 1–5 manager ratings |
| Growth Trend | 10% | Linear regression slope of weekly revenue |
| Stability Index | 10% | Consistency score based on coefficient of variation |
| App Conversion Rate | 10% | App downloads per bill, normalized to dept average |
| Attendance Rate | 3% | Verified present days / total working days |
| Punctuality Score | 2% | On-time check-ins relative to shift start |

### Derived Metrics
- **Stability Index** — `(1 - CoeffientOfVariation) × 100` — rewards consistency over volatility
- **Growth Trend** — linear regression slope over weekly revenues, normalized across all employees
- **Basket Performance Index** — employee basket size divided by department average, removes category bias

